FIREWALL MANAGEMENT COMMANDS
**********************************
1.Check the firewall state
 command : firewall-cmd --state

2.View the current firewall rules
 command : firewall-cmd --list-all

3.Show the configure port numbers
 command : firewall-cmd --list-ports

4.Firewall host configuration to allow the port number 
 command : firewall-cmd --permanent --add-port=(port number)/tcp

 example : firewall-cmd --permanent --add-port=8080/tcp

5.Make the port number active
 command : firewall-cmd --reload

6.Check the allowed services in the current zone
 command : firewall-cmd --list-services
 
7.Add the services
  command : firewall-cmd --permanent --add-service=http
        firewall-cmd --reload                       |
                                                 example  
 > check the if the service is add :firewall-cmd --list-services
                                                   
8.Remove the added services temporarly (after reboot came back again)
   command : firewall-cmd --remove-service=http
       firewall-cmd --reload <-----------> applied the saved configs

9.Remove the added service permanently 
  command : firewall-cmd --permanent --remove-sevices=http
    firewall-cmd --reload

10.Remove the added port numbers
   command : firewall-cmd --remove-port=8080/tcp
     firewall-cmd --reload               |
                                       example

11.Check the active zones
  whcich is active 
  which network interfaced is attached
  how firewall applies the traffic rules

  command : firewall-cmd --get-active-zones

12.List avliable services

 command : firewall-cmd --get-services 

**************************************************************
FIREWALL SEVICE COMMANDS
**************************************************************
13.Check the status firewalld

 command : systemctl status firewalld

14.Start firewalld

 command : systemctl start firewalld

15.Enable the firewall

 command : systemctl enable firewalld

16.Restart the firewalld

 command : systemctl restart firewalld

17.Disable the firewalld after reboot

 command : systemctl disable firewalld

**************************************************
ZONE COMMANDS
**************************************************
18.Show the default zone

 command : firewall-cmd --get-default-zone

19.List all rules in a specific zone

 command : firewall-cmd --zone=public --list-all

20.Change default zone

 command : firewall-cmd --set-default-zone=public 
 